Webinar with several participants and presentators

=Description=

"Courier co‑ops have become even more relevant with the COVID‑19 crisis. This webinar introduced the idea of courier co‑ops. There are a number of courier businesses run as a co-operative internationally, but only a handful in the UK.

Hear from:

– CoopCycle, the platform co‑op that provides infrastructure for courier co‑ops across Europe
– Co‑op Culture, experts in supporting co-operative, community and social enterprises to start and grow.
– York Collective, the UK's first cycle courier co‑op

The conversation was facilitated by Co‑operatives UK's Ludovica Rogers, who leads on the UnFound programme for tech founders and start-ups looking for a different way to set-up and run platform businesses."

